            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bge_M3_FP16 is a half-precision variant of the BGE M3 embedding model, designed for efficient text representation. It supports multilingual inputs, with embedding dimensions of 1024 and a max sequence length of 8192 tokens. The FP16 quantization reduces memory usage by approximately 50% compared to FP32, enabling lower latency and higher throughput in API deployments."
